"response_text": "The cumulative harvest of postpartum female prey by forager bands initiates at zero and exhibits a dominant upward trajectory throughout the majority of the simulation. The aggregate value ascends consistently, reaching a peak average of 119.0 around step 1826, before settling at a final value of 117.0 by the conclusion of the 2312-step run. Structural breaks in the trend are evident at steps 475, 625, and 850, signaling distinct phases in the predation pressure or availability of the target demographic.\n\nStatistical trend analysis confirms a robust increasing pattern for the first 1391 steps, after which the rate of accumulation moderates. A window of no clear trend appears between steps 1392 and 1623, followed by a phase indicating a slight reduction in the mean accumulation rate towards the end of the run. In the context of the model, this pattern reflects the high priority foragers place on reproductive females, depleting this high-value segment of the herd population efficiently over time."
}

